Sudan shut the airports in March as part of measures to curb the spread of the coronavirus pandemic. It has been reviewing the closure every two weeks. Airports are open only for flights transporting cargo, humanitarian aid, oil organisationsâ€™ workers or evacuating foreigners, said Abdul Hafiz Abdul Rahim, the SCAA spokesperson. Sudan had reported 7007 coronavirus infections as of Thursday, including 447 deaths, the Health Ministry said. --Reuters--